                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d237">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.20/732: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-18T19:00:00+00:00"
                            >March 18, 1935—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 18—3:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>117. Report from Berlin states that Germans gave immediate favorable answer to
                    British Ambassador when he presented note contained in my 116, March 18, 5
                    p.m.</p>
                <p>Foreign Office has just informed press that Simon and Eden will leave for Berlin
                    Sunday as planned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
